<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-02-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Snowden</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-02-14"><hi rend="italic">February 14,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Snowden is informed that the United States rely on the sense of justice
                        of Spain to meet our just expectations. The assurances given by Spain in
                        1886 make arbitration as unnecessary as it is unacceptable.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Foster.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>